      "description": "This 996.2 Carrera is a mechanically sound example of Porsche\u2019s rear-engine legacy, powered by the 3.6L M96 flat-six engine. The powertrain is mated to a G96 6-speed manual transaxle, ensuring a direct mechanical connection and precise gear synchronization. Critical preventative maintenance has been addressed, including an LN Engineering IMS bearing retrofit and a proactive rear main seal replacement to ensure long-term crankcase integrity. The chassis retains its factory-spec handling characteristics via a multi-link rear suspension and MacPherson struts, while the braking system utilizes four-piston Monobloc calipers over ventilated rotors for high-thermal-capacity deceleration. The induction system remains free of vacuum leaks, providing a crisp throttle response across the rev range. While the finish shows minor road-wear consistent with its age, the structural rigidity and drivetrain harmonics are excellent, making this a focused driver\u2019s car for the technical enthusiast.",
